===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|艸|介|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p|t1=grass, plant}} – a type of plant.

===Etymology===
The meaning "mustard green" is attested earliest in the ''{{w|Book of Rites}}''; "small grass" in ''{{w|Zuo zhuan}}'' (Ai 1).

{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} compares it to {{cog|okm|갓}}, {{cog|tai-swe-pro|*ka:tᴰ}} (> {{cog|th|กาด}}, {{cog|lo|ກາດ}}, {{cog|shn|ၵၢတ်ႇ}}), {{cog|mkh-vie-pro|*kaːs}} (> {{cog|vi|cải}}, {{cog|mtq|cái}}, & {{cog|thm|-}} ''kajh¹''). However, all those foreign items might have been loaned from Late Old Chinese or {{w|Eastern Han Chinese}} (as proposed by Pittayaporn for {{m|tai-pro|*ka:tᴰ}}),

